the program, are playbooks and
network protocol analyzers.

76
00:03:24.525 --> 00:03:25.880
A playbook is a manual that

77
00:03:25.880 --> 00:03:28.625
provides details about
any operational action,

78
00:03:28.625 --> 00:03:30.905
such as how to respond
to an incident.

79
00:03:30.905 --> 00:03:34.550
Playbooks, which vary from one
organization to the next,

80
00:03:34.550 --> 00:03:36.110
guide analysts in how to

81
00:03:36.110 --> 00:03:38.240
handle a security
incident before,

82
00:03:38.240 --> 00:03:41.105
during, and after
it has occurred.

83
00:03:41.105 --> 00:03:43.700
Playbooks can pertain
to security or

84
00:03:43.700 --> 00:03:46.040
compliance reviews,
access management,

85
00:03:46.040 --> 00:03:48.380
and many other
organizational tasks that

86
00:03:48.380 --> 00:03:51.755
require a documented process
from beginning to end.

87
00:03:52.755 --> 00:03:53.510
Another tool you may use as

88
00:03:53.510 --> 00:03:57.035
a security analyst is a
network protocol analyzer,

89
00:03:57.035 --> 00:03:59.380
also called packet sniffer.

90
00:03:59.380 --> 00:04:02.390
A packet sniffer is
a tool designed to

91
00:04:02.390 --> 00:04:05.600
capture and analyze data
traffic within a network.

92
00:04:05.600 --> 00:04:08.000
Common network
protocol analyzers

93
00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:11.560
include tcpdump and Wireshark.

94
00:04:12.560 --> 00:04:13.355
As an entry-level analyst,

95
00:04:13.355 --> 00:04:15.680
you don't have to be an
expert in these tools.

